<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Dumbbell-Hammer-Wrist-Curl">Dumbbell Hammer Wrist Curl</h3>



<p>The <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/dumbbell-hammer-wrist-curl" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">dumbbell hammer wrist twist</a> uses an isolated wrist movement with a neutral grip position. Keeping your elbows resting on your thighs while slightly bent over places the primary focus on your brachioradialis. Your brachialis, wrist flexors, and wrist extensors perform secondary roles.</p>



<p>Performing dumbbell hammer wrist twists improves wrist flexibility and builds grip strength. This helps to improve function and reduce <a href="https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC8038891/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">possible injury risk</a> in common weight-bearing activities.</p>



