<li>Bring your torso forward and rest your elbows on your thighs. Your forearms should be parallel to the ground while holding the dumbbells with a neutral grip (palms facing in).&nbsp;</li>



<li>Your head should be in a neutral position looking at the floor in front of you. Keep a neutral back with your chest up.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Inhale and engage your core. Exhale and lift the dumbbells using your wrists. Your forearms should stay in the same position.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Pause briefly as you come to the top range of motion.</li>



<li>Inhale and bring the dumbbells down under control.&nbsp;</li>
