<h2 class="wp-block-heading list-start">Anatomy Of The Forearm</h2>



<p>We can split the <a href="https://www.mdpi.com/2075-1729/12/2/188" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">main forearm muscles</a> into the wrist flexors, wrist extensors, and brachioradialis. Each varies in location and function. Let&#8217;s take a look at each of them in more detail.&nbsp;</p>


